I'm not sure why eclipse is trying to access
plugins\org.eclipse.jdt.source_3.1.1\src\org.junit_3.8.1\junitsrc.zip

1) downloading eclipse-JDT-SDK-3.2RC3.zip
2) copied over org.eclipse.jdt.source_3.2.0.v20060428-0010-F7snp5ffnngadgn
3) finally, rename it org.eclipse.jdt.source_3.1.1

plugins\org.eclipse.jdt.source_3.1.1\src\org.junit_3.8.1\junitsrc.zip

Maybe debug should log these exceptions but better ignore the non-existing source location.
